WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.988 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.988 --> 00:00:04.446 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.446 --> 00:00:32.130 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:35.220 align:middle line:10%
>> Your reality is created
by your thought about it,

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:38.363 align:middle line:10%
and by the word you speak and
the actions that you undertake.

00:00:38.363 --> 00:00:39.780 align:middle line:10%
Therefore, the
first thing we have

00:00:39.780 --> 00:00:42.870 align:middle line:10%
to eliminate from our mind in
the process of manifestation

00:00:42.870 --> 00:00:45.990 align:middle line:10%
is we have to eliminate any
thought that we do not now

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:48.210 align:middle line:10%
have, or, in the
words of some people,

00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:49.680 align:middle line:10%
that we somehow
can't have, there's

00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:51.600 align:middle line:10%
some reason why
we can't have what

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:56.340 align:middle line:10%
it is we choose to experience
in life, but rather to say,

00:00:56.340 --> 00:00:58.620 align:middle line:10%
with all the faith
we can muster,

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:03.390 align:middle line:10%
not only can I have that,
I have that right now.

00:01:03.390 --> 00:01:09.690 align:middle line:10%
>> Wouldn't it be wonderful to
have a conversation with God?

00:01:09.690 --> 00:01:13.870 align:middle line:84%
Well, we have someone here
today who actually has done it,

00:01:13.870 --> 00:01:16.480 align:middle line:84%
and is going to teach us
maybe how you can do it.

00:01:16.480 --> 00:01:18.165 align:middle line:84%
And of course, for
the one or two people

00:01:18.165 --> 00:01:19.770 align:middle line:84%
who don't know who
that is, that's

00:01:19.770 --> 00:01:24.810 align:middle line:84%
Neale Donald Walsch, who has
completed his third volume

00:01:24.810 --> 00:01:26.550 align:middle line:90%
of "Conversations with God."

00:01:26.550 --> 00:01:27.583 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:01:27.583 --> 00:01:28.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you, Corrine.

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:29.190 align:middle line:90%
It's nice to be here.

00:01:29.190 --> 00:01:30.760 align:middle line:84%
>> We are so thrilled
to have you back.

00:01:30.760 --> 00:01:31.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, it's good to be back.

00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:32.280 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:34.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, there are one or two
people in the audience who

00:01:34.680 --> 00:01:37.860 align:middle line:84%
don't know the history of
how you happened to have

00:01:37.860 --> 00:01:40.980 align:middle line:90%
a conversation with God.

00:01:40.980 --> 00:01:43.830 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, it all started
[INAUDIBLE] in 1992,

00:01:43.830 --> 00:01:47.483 align:middle line:10%
when I reached a low point in
my life and I called out to God.

00:01:47.483 --> 00:01:48.900 align:middle line:10%
And I asked the
kinds of questions

00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:50.790 align:middle line:10%
that we all ask at
times like that.

00:01:50.790 --> 00:01:52.290 align:middle line:84%
What does it take
to make life work?

00:01:52.290 --> 00:01:53.707 align:middle line:84%
What have I done
to deserve a life

00:01:53.707 --> 00:01:55.590 align:middle line:90%
of such continuing struggle?

00:01:55.590 --> 00:01:58.290 align:middle line:84%
And help me to understand
how to get from where

00:01:58.290 --> 00:02:00.510 align:middle line:90%
I am to where I want to be.

00:02:00.510 --> 00:02:03.840 align:middle line:84%
And in this case, much
to my shock and surprise,

00:02:03.840 --> 00:02:04.830 align:middle line:90%
God answered.

00:02:04.830 --> 00:02:07.140 align:middle line:84%
My calling out came in the
form of an angry letter

00:02:07.140 --> 00:02:08.530 align:middle line:84%
that I wrote in the
middle of the night.

00:02:08.530 --> 00:02:09.905 align:middle line:84%
At four o'clock
in the morning, I

00:02:09.905 --> 00:02:12.630 align:middle line:84%
woke up with great frustration,
marched out to the living room,

00:02:12.630 --> 00:02:15.450 align:middle line:84%
where I was sitting
in the living room,

00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:17.630 align:middle line:84%
and I saw a yellow legal
pad on the coffee table,

00:02:17.630 --> 00:02:21.030 align:middle line:84%
so I began to write an angry
letter to the universe with all

00:02:21.030 --> 00:02:22.498 align:middle line:90%
those angry questions.

00:02:22.498 --> 00:02:23.790 align:middle line:90%
>> How could you do this to me?

00:02:23.790 --> 00:02:25.082 align:middle line:90%
>> How could you do this to me?

00:02:25.082 --> 00:02:26.260 align:middle line:90%
After all I've done for you.

00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:27.510 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:02:27.510 --> 00:02:30.320 align:middle line:84%
>> And there I was, sitting
in my pool of anger,

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:32.820 align:middle line:84%
when I heard a voiceless
voice that said to me, Neale,

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:35.550 align:middle line:84%
do you really want answers
to all of these questions,

00:02:35.550 --> 00:02:37.620 align:middle line:90%
or are you just venting?

00:02:37.620 --> 00:02:39.810 align:middle line:84%
And I wrote-- I can
recall the moment--

00:02:39.810 --> 00:02:42.150 align:middle line:84%
I am venting, but if you have
answers, I'd sure as heck

00:02:42.150 --> 00:02:44.100 align:middle line:90%
like to know what they are.

00:02:44.100 --> 00:02:46.980 align:middle line:84%
And then I was given the
answers to all those questions

00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:50.080 align:middle line:84%
I had written, and to questions
I hadn't even thought about.

00:02:50.080 --> 00:02:53.070 align:middle line:84%
And as I began hearing those
answers, really in my head,

00:02:53.070 --> 00:02:57.022 align:middle line:84%
as a voiceless voice, other
questions came up for me.

00:02:57.022 --> 00:02:58.980 align:middle line:84%
And I began to answer
those questions, as well.

00:02:58.980 --> 00:03:00.300 align:middle line:90%
And the result was--

00:03:00.300 --> 00:03:01.710 align:middle line:90%
that's the short story--

00:03:01.710 --> 00:03:03.630 align:middle line:84%
a wonderful 3 and
1/2 year dialogue

00:03:03.630 --> 00:03:06.540 align:middle line:84%
which has produced an
extraordinary trilogy of books,

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:08.130 align:middle line:84%
never really
intended to be books.

00:03:08.130 --> 00:03:11.460 align:middle line:84%
It was always a private
process going on with me

00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:13.830 align:middle line:84%
in the privacy of my own
heart and my own soul

00:03:13.830 --> 00:03:15.330 align:middle line:90%
and my own mind.

00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:19.510 align:middle line:84%
But it wound up turning into a
series of best-selling books.

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:21.690 align:middle line:84%
>> The first book,
"Conversations with God,"

00:03:21.690 --> 00:03:23.670 align:middle line:90%
surprised everyone.

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:24.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:28.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Because it remained,
and I think still remains,

00:03:28.260 --> 00:03:30.510 align:middle line:84%
on the bestseller list
after a couple of years.

00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:31.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:33.330 align:middle line:90%
For over 95 weeks.

00:03:33.330 --> 00:03:37.518 align:middle line:84%
>> Why are people so interested
in what God has said to you?

00:03:37.518 --> 00:03:39.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Because, Corrine, I think
that people, first of all,

00:03:39.810 --> 00:03:41.490 align:middle line:84%
share my experience,
to some degree,

00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:44.530 align:middle line:84%
my experience of frustration
with life as it's now being

00:03:44.530 --> 00:03:45.330 align:middle line:90%
lived.

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:47.350 align:middle line:84%
Not that all of us
are having a bad time,

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:49.980 align:middle line:84%
but we see the world in a
place that we don't think

00:03:49.980 --> 00:03:53.380 align:middle line:84%
it should be, given all of
our own best intentions.

00:03:53.380 --> 00:03:55.230 align:middle line:84%
So the universe,
the world has begun

00:03:55.230 --> 00:03:56.650 align:middle line:90%
to lose patience with itself.

00:03:56.650 --> 00:03:59.760 align:middle line:84%
We can see that this is
not the way it ought to be,

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:02.700 align:middle line:84%
the way life is now being
lived on our planet.

00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:06.000 align:middle line:84%
And that frustration has driven
the engine of their experience

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:06.870 align:middle line:90%
of searching.

00:04:06.870 --> 00:04:09.120 align:middle line:84%
If that isn't the
way, then what is?

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:10.800 align:middle line:84%
And of course, if
somebody writes a book

00:04:10.800 --> 00:04:12.883 align:middle line:84%
and said I had a conversation
with God about this,

00:04:12.883 --> 00:04:14.520 align:middle line:90%
that's pretty hard to resist.

00:04:14.520 --> 00:04:16.470 align:middle line:84%
So people wind up
reading the book.

00:04:16.470 --> 00:04:19.399 align:middle line:84%
And then they, much
to their astonishment,

00:04:19.399 --> 00:04:21.763 align:middle line:84%
agree was 95% of what
they're reading there.

00:04:21.763 --> 00:04:23.680 align:middle line:84%
Nobody should agree with
all of it, of course.

00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:25.390 align:middle line:90%
I'd be real upset if they did.

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:27.240 align:middle line:84%
I'd be a little bit
frightened of that.

00:04:27.240 --> 00:04:30.120 align:middle line:84%
But people are finding a
large place of agreement

00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:33.383 align:middle line:84%
with most of what they're
reading in these three books.

00:04:33.383 --> 00:04:35.550 align:middle line:84%
So I think what's happening
is that people have come

00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:37.460 align:middle line:84%
to the same conclusions
I've come to,

00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:40.620 align:middle line:90%
that there's a better way.

00:04:40.620 --> 00:04:43.230 align:middle line:84%
And the book outlines what
those better ways might be.

00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:46.110 align:middle line:84%
So the books have become,
as a result, very popular.

00:04:46.110 --> 00:04:47.730 align:middle line:84%
>> What are we
doing wrong, Neale?

00:04:47.730 --> 00:04:50.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Everything, just about.

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:54.600 align:middle line:84%
It starts, Corrine, with our
understanding of who we are

00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:58.360 align:middle line:84%
and how it is for
us as human beings.

00:04:58.360 --> 00:05:01.350 align:middle line:84%
And the largest misunderstanding
is that there's more than one

00:05:01.350 --> 00:05:03.270 align:middle line:90%
of us in the room.

00:05:03.270 --> 00:05:05.880 align:middle line:84%
People think that there's
you and there's me,

00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:07.540 align:middle line:84%
that there's him
and there's her,

00:05:07.540 --> 00:05:09.660 align:middle line:84%
that there's that
country and that country,

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:13.380 align:middle line:84%
and they don't really understand
that there's only one of us.

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:17.100 align:middle line:84%
So the basic misunderstanding,
the first cultural myth

00:05:17.100 --> 00:05:19.020 align:middle line:84%
that drives the engine
of our experience

00:05:19.020 --> 00:05:21.150 align:middle line:84%
in the wrong
direction is the myth

00:05:21.150 --> 00:05:23.670 align:middle line:84%
that we're somehow
separate from each other.

00:05:23.670 --> 00:05:27.270 align:middle line:84%
That myth is born in a
larger misunderstanding

00:05:27.270 --> 00:05:29.790 align:middle line:84%
that we're somehow
separate from God.

00:05:29.790 --> 00:05:31.770 align:middle line:90%
Both statements are untrue.

00:05:31.770 --> 00:05:34.620 align:middle line:84%
But when we start from
such a place of untruths,

00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:38.100 align:middle line:84%
from such a lack of
understanding, all of the other

00:05:38.100 --> 00:05:43.610 align:middle line:84%
experiences that we
co-create are also

00:05:43.610 --> 00:05:44.820 align:middle line:90%
sent in the wrong direction.

00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:46.620 align:middle line:84%
They're experiences
that don't get us

00:05:46.620 --> 00:05:48.720 align:middle line:90%
where we say we want to go.

00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:50.670 align:middle line:84%
The result is we have
a human race that's

00:05:50.670 --> 00:05:53.310 align:middle line:84%
saying it wants to go one
place, and is really winding up

00:05:53.310 --> 00:05:54.520 align:middle line:90%
in quite another place.

00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:55.320 align:middle line:90%
We don't know why.

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:56.730 align:middle line:90%
We don't know how we got here.

00:05:56.730 --> 00:05:59.410 align:middle line:84%
We look over our shoulder and
say, how did this all happen?

00:05:59.410 --> 00:06:01.415 align:middle line:84%
We can't even really
put it all together.

00:06:01.415 --> 00:06:02.790 align:middle line:84%
But we know how
to get out of it.

00:06:02.790 --> 00:06:05.490 align:middle line:84%
The way to get out of it is
to change our idea that we're

00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:07.330 align:middle line:90%
separate from each other.

00:06:07.330 --> 00:06:09.390 align:middle line:84%
There are several
other cultural myths

00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:12.030 align:middle line:84%
that have also been
mistaken and come

00:06:12.030 --> 00:06:14.070 align:middle line:84%
under the heading of
what we're doing wrong.

00:06:14.070 --> 00:06:16.230 align:middle line:84%
The second one is that we
think that there is not

00:06:16.230 --> 00:06:18.210 align:middle line:84%
enough of all the
good things in life.

00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:22.710 align:middle line:84%
We believe in a life of
insufficiency, a life of lack.

00:06:22.710 --> 00:06:26.740 align:middle line:84%
And God tells us in the
dialogues that there is enough.

00:06:26.740 --> 00:06:28.680 align:middle line:84%
In fact, that's
the rich statement

00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:31.130 align:middle line:90%
that's made-- there is enough.

00:06:31.130 --> 00:06:32.910 align:middle line:84%
Now, if we thought
there was enough--

00:06:32.910 --> 00:06:37.230 align:middle line:84%
enough food, enough money,
enough energy, enough oil,

00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.412 align:middle line:84%
enough of land or
whatever that we

00:06:39.412 --> 00:06:40.620 align:middle line:90%
think there's not enough of--

00:06:40.620 --> 00:06:41.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Enough health.

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:44.950 align:middle line:84%
>> --enough health-- if we
thought there was enough of all

00:06:44.950 --> 00:06:47.110 align:middle line:84%
the things we need
in life to be happy,

00:06:47.110 --> 00:06:50.260 align:middle line:84%
we'd begin to find a way to
share it more appropriately

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:51.910 align:middle line:90%
and more freely with others.

00:06:51.910 --> 00:06:53.560 align:middle line:90%
What stops us from sharing--

00:06:53.560 --> 00:06:56.980 align:middle line:84%
even health, by the way, which
is not shared in this country,

00:06:56.980 --> 00:06:59.740 align:middle line:84%
and in most places
on this planet

00:06:59.740 --> 00:07:01.450 align:middle line:90%
in the form of health care--

00:07:01.450 --> 00:07:03.850 align:middle line:84%
we can't find it in
our hearts to provide

00:07:03.850 --> 00:07:07.540 align:middle line:84%
even the minimal adequate health
care for all of our brothers

00:07:07.540 --> 00:07:09.010 align:middle line:90%
and sisters on the planet.

00:07:09.010 --> 00:07:10.978 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you have
enough money, of course,

00:07:10.978 --> 00:07:12.520 align:middle line:84%
you can have access
to all the health

00:07:12.520 --> 00:07:14.330 align:middle line:90%
care you could possibly want.

00:07:14.330 --> 00:07:17.410 align:middle line:84%
But if you're one of the 95%
of the people on the planet who

00:07:17.410 --> 00:07:19.360 align:middle line:84%
don't have that kind of
money, well, then you

00:07:19.360 --> 00:07:20.620 align:middle line:90%
take your chances.

00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:23.890 align:middle line:84%
What kind of a humane race
would set it up that way?

00:07:23.890 --> 00:07:26.110 align:middle line:84%
So we're a very
primitive species

00:07:26.110 --> 00:07:30.080 align:middle line:84%
trying to bumble along
in our misunderstandings.

00:07:30.080 --> 00:07:31.827 align:middle line:84%
The books, however,
set things right.

00:07:31.827 --> 00:07:33.660 align:middle line:84%
All you have to do,
therefore, is read them.

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:35.618 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we also have to
do something about it.

00:07:35.618 --> 00:07:38.860 align:middle line:84%
For example, we have to change
the way we have been thinking.

00:07:38.860 --> 00:07:40.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:40.720 --> 00:07:46.990 align:middle line:84%
>> The difference between your
book and pretty much 99% of all

00:07:46.990 --> 00:07:50.950 align:middle line:84%
the other metaphysical work
that's out there is that

00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:53.330 align:middle line:84%
the other metaphysical works
says we're here to learn

00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:54.460 align:middle line:90%
our lessons.

00:07:54.460 --> 00:07:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:55.630 --> 00:08:00.230 align:middle line:84%
>> And your book says
we're here to experience.

00:08:00.230 --> 00:08:02.260 align:middle line:84%
>> And remember
who we really are.

00:08:02.260 --> 00:08:04.870 align:middle line:84%
To experience who we
really are and to remember

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:06.010 align:middle line:90%
who we really are.

00:08:06.010 --> 00:08:09.160 align:middle line:84%
And then, Corrine, to
recreate ourselves anew

00:08:09.160 --> 00:08:12.640 align:middle line:84%
in the next grandest version
of the greatest vision we ever

00:08:12.640 --> 00:08:14.960 align:middle line:90%
held about who we are.

00:08:14.960 --> 00:08:16.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's the missing
element, and that's

00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:20.110 align:middle line:84%
what we're not doing, because
we keep on insisting that we're

00:08:20.110 --> 00:08:21.210 align:middle line:90%
here to learn some lesson.

00:08:21.210 --> 00:08:23.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you think you're
here to learn a lesson

00:08:23.210 --> 00:08:25.252 align:middle line:84%
and you're clearly and
obviously not learning it,

00:08:25.252 --> 00:08:28.262 align:middle line:84%
then you'll keep on continuing
behaviors thinking that,

00:08:28.262 --> 00:08:29.470 align:middle line:90%
well, one day, I'll learn it.

00:08:29.470 --> 00:08:32.890 align:middle line:84%
If I keep on doing this, I'll
learn how to do it better.

00:08:32.890 --> 00:08:36.460 align:middle line:84%
The approach to life
that masters take

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:39.870 align:middle line:84%
is to know that it's not
about learning anything.

00:08:39.870 --> 00:08:41.470 align:middle line:84%
We're not here to
learn a lesson,

00:08:41.470 --> 00:08:45.910 align:middle line:84%
but rather to remember something
we've always known and are

00:08:45.910 --> 00:08:47.710 align:middle line:90%
simply not applying.

00:08:47.710 --> 00:08:50.800 align:middle line:84%
No one needs to tell
many people, truly,

00:08:50.800 --> 00:08:53.890 align:middle line:84%
what it is like to love, what
it is like to feel compassion,

00:08:53.890 --> 00:08:55.090 align:middle line:90%
one for the other.

00:08:55.090 --> 00:08:57.670 align:middle line:84%
These are I almost want
to say cellular memories.

00:08:57.670 --> 00:09:00.040 align:middle line:90%
These are built-in responses.

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:03.190 align:middle line:84%
There is hardly a person on
the planet, even the toughest,

00:09:03.190 --> 00:09:05.980 align:middle line:84%
roughest among us, who
would not feel compassion

00:09:05.980 --> 00:09:07.705 align:middle line:90%
under certain circumstances.

00:09:07.705 --> 00:09:09.580 align:middle line:84%
The question is, why
don't we feel compassion

00:09:09.580 --> 00:09:12.920 align:middle line:84%
under all circumstances,
and for all people?

00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:15.730 align:middle line:84%
And so these are responses
that are built into us.

00:09:15.730 --> 00:09:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And what we have to do now
is remember who we really are

00:09:19.570 --> 00:09:21.460 align:middle line:84%
and what the truth
of our soul is

00:09:21.460 --> 00:09:25.100 align:middle line:84%
at times when the exterior
circumstances of our lives

00:09:25.100 --> 00:09:28.240 align:middle line:84%
seem to want us
make us forget that.

00:09:28.240 --> 00:09:32.920 align:middle line:84%
>> The thing that is most
startling is, it says,

00:09:32.920 --> 00:09:35.570 align:middle line:84%
that whatever you came here,
this is not God's test to come

00:09:35.570 --> 00:09:36.370 align:middle line:90%
down here.

00:09:36.370 --> 00:09:37.540 align:middle line:90%
These are not lessons.

00:09:37.540 --> 00:09:38.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:09:38.440 --> 00:09:42.070 align:middle line:84%
>> That whatever you have
created in your life you can

00:09:42.070 --> 00:09:45.410 align:middle line:90%
change, because you created it.

00:09:45.410 --> 00:09:48.310 align:middle line:84%
And you talk about the
process of manifesting

00:09:48.310 --> 00:09:49.720 align:middle line:90%
whatever you like.

00:09:49.720 --> 00:09:53.540 align:middle line:84%
>> God designed us in
his image and likeness.

00:09:53.540 --> 00:09:55.600 align:middle line:90%
And God is a three-part being.

00:09:55.600 --> 00:09:57.670 align:middle line:84%
Some theologies called
these three parts

00:09:57.670 --> 00:10:00.590 align:middle line:84%
God the Father, God the
Son, and God the Holy Ghost.

00:10:00.590 --> 00:10:02.882 align:middle line:84%
And there are other ways of
defining those three parts,

00:10:02.882 --> 00:10:03.682 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:10:03.682 --> 00:10:05.860 align:middle line:84%
The conscious, the subconscious,
the superconscious,

00:10:05.860 --> 00:10:07.420 align:middle line:90%
if you're into psychology.

00:10:07.420 --> 00:10:10.000 align:middle line:84%
Virtually every
discipline, whether it's

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:12.400 align:middle line:84%
theology, psychology,
or raw science,

00:10:12.400 --> 00:10:15.370 align:middle line:84%
has some way of describing
the triumvirate,

00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:18.790 align:middle line:84%
the three-part beingness
that is all of life.

00:10:18.790 --> 00:10:21.730 align:middle line:84%
And what God said to
me in the dialogue

00:10:21.730 --> 00:10:24.220 align:middle line:84%
is that we are also
three-part beings,

00:10:24.220 --> 00:10:27.610 align:middle line:84%
and that we create from
three aspects of the self.

00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:30.490 align:middle line:84%
And those three tools of
creation that we're all given

00:10:30.490 --> 00:10:32.260 align:middle line:90%
are thought, word, and deed.

00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:35.410 align:middle line:10%
That we create with our
thoughts, with our words,

00:10:35.410 --> 00:10:38.230 align:middle line:10%
and with our actions, and
that each one of those three

00:10:38.230 --> 00:10:40.353 align:middle line:10%
elements is created
in and of itself,

00:10:40.353 --> 00:10:41.770 align:middle line:10%
and when we have
all three of them

00:10:41.770 --> 00:10:45.160 align:middle line:10%
together, when we're
thinking and saying and doing

00:10:45.160 --> 00:10:48.910 align:middle line:10%
the same thing, then we become
really very, very powerful.

00:10:48.910 --> 00:10:50.410 align:middle line:84%
And we produce
results in our lives,

00:10:50.410 --> 00:10:53.750 align:middle line:84%
and in the lives of others,
I might add, very quickly.

00:10:53.750 --> 00:10:57.190 align:middle line:84%
>> We are talking to
Neale Donald Walsch about

00:10:57.190 --> 00:11:00.470 align:middle line:84%
"Conversations with
God Book Three."

00:11:00.470 --> 00:11:02.200 align:middle line:84%
And if you hang
out with us today,

00:11:02.200 --> 00:11:06.645 align:middle line:84%
you may find out how you can get
anything you want in your life.

00:11:06.645 --> 00:11:07.810 align:middle line:90%
So stay with us.

00:11:07.810 --> 00:11:09.478 align:middle line:90%
We'll be right back.

00:11:09.478 --> 00:11:13.350 align:middle line:90%
